%I A397235 #19 Jun 19 2026 09:38:56
%S A397235 1,2,5,11,26,60,140,325,756,1757,4085,9496,22076,51320,119305,277350,
%T A397235 644761,1498887,3484490,8100456,18831276,43777405,101770120,236586825,
%U A397235 549997641,1278589392,2972359720,6909898016,16063564001,37343255690,86812537085,201814663875
%N A397235 Expansion of 1/(1 - 2*x - x^2 + x^3 - x^4).
%H A397235 <a href="/index/Rec#order_04">Index entries for linear recurrences with constant coefficients</a>, signature (2,1,-1,1).
%F A397235 a(n) = 2*a(n-1) + a(n-2) - a(n-3) + a(n-4).
%F A397235 G.f.: 1/( (1+x) * (1-3*x+2*x^2-x^3) ).
%F A397235 Let Sum_{n>=0} b(n) * x^n = 1/( P(x^s) * Q(x^s)^(s-1-k) * R(x^s)^k * (Q(x^s) - x^m * R(x^s)) ), where s >= 2, m >= 1, 0 <= k <= s-1, gcd(m,s)=1, and P(0)*Q(0)*R(0) != 0. Then Sum_{n>=0} b(s*n+m*k) * x^n = 1/( P(x) * (Q(x)^s - x^m * R(x)^s) ).
%F A397235 Here s=3, m=2, k=2, P(x)=1+x, Q(x)=1-x, R(x)=1, and b(n) = A079955(n). Therefore a(n) = b(3*n+4) = A079955(3*n+4), and Sum_{n>=0} a(n) * x^n = 1/(1 - 2*x - x^2 + x^3 - x^4).
%o A397235 (PARI) my(N=40, x='x+O('x^N)); Vec(1/(1-2*x-x^2+x^3-x^4))
%Y A397235 Cf. A079955.
%K A397235 nonn,easy
%O A397235 0,2
%A A397235 _Seiichi Manyama_, Jun 19 2026
